2016 WW50 Bakerville/SKX-D BKC Release Announcement (BKC #3)

\n \n \n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2016 WW50 Bakerville/SKX-D BKC release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n Linux/\n \n VMWare/\n \n Windows\n server. The auto-installer packages are available on the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Bei, Ling.

Test Result:

\xc2\xb7       Finish BKC test execution on\nRHEL 7.2 and Windows2016. Please visit HPQC for test details. Refer to the installation guide for\nthe BKC package installation

\xc2\xb7      Bakerville(RP Board: Yuba\nCity RP\nfab3)

o   Total test cases: 117; Passed test cases is 102 and pass\nrate is 87.18%. 

o   Test coverage:  

\xc2\xa7     SKX-D L0 VIS SoC: Run P1  test cases on RHEL 7.2 and Windows2016.
